ReplicationJob

data ReplicationJob Source #

Represents a replication job.

See: newReplicationJob smart constructor.

Constructors

ReplicationJob' 

Fields

  • nextReplicationRunStartTime :: Maybe POSIX

    The start time of the next replication run.

  • numberOfRecentAmisToKeep :: Maybe Int

    The number of recent AMIs to keep in the customer's account for a replication job. By default, the value is set to zero, meaning that all AMIs are kept.

  • statusMessage :: Maybe Text

    The description of the current status of the replication job.

  • encrypted :: Maybe Bool

    Indicates whether the replication job should produce encrypted AMIs.

  • latestAmiId :: Maybe Text

    The ID of the latest Amazon Machine Image (AMI).

  • roleName :: Maybe Text

    The name of the IAM role to be used by AWS SMS.

  • serverId :: Maybe Text

    The ID of the server.

  • state :: Maybe ReplicationJobState

    The state of the replication job.

  • kmsKeyId :: Maybe Text

    The ID of the KMS key for replication jobs that produce encrypted AMIs. This value can be any of the following:

    • KMS key ID
    • KMS key alias
    • ARN referring to the KMS key ID
    • ARN referring to the KMS key alias

    If encrypted is enabled but a KMS key ID is not specified, the customer's default KMS key for Amazon EBS is used.

  • replicationRunList :: Maybe [ReplicationRun]

    Information about the replication runs.

  • frequency :: Maybe Int

    The time between consecutive replication runs, in hours.

  • replicationJobId :: Maybe Text

    The ID of the replication job.

  • runOnce :: Maybe Bool

    Indicates whether to run the replication job one time.

  • seedReplicationTime :: Maybe POSIX

    The seed replication time.

  • description :: Maybe Text

    The description of the replication job.

  • vmServer :: Maybe VmServer

    Information about the VM server.

  • licenseType :: Maybe LicenseType

    The license type to be used for the AMI created by a successful replication run.

  • serverType :: Maybe ServerType

    The type of server.

ServerReplicationParameters

data ServerReplicationParameters Source #

The replication parameters for replicating a server.

See: newServerReplicationParameters smart constructor.

Constructors

ServerReplicationParameters' 

Fields

  • numberOfRecentAmisToKeep :: Maybe Int

    The number of recent AMIs to keep when creating a replication job for this server.

  • encrypted :: Maybe Bool

    Indicates whether the replication job produces encrypted AMIs.

  • seedTime :: Maybe POSIX

    The seed time for creating a replication job for the server.

  • kmsKeyId :: Maybe Text

    The ID of the KMS key for replication jobs that produce encrypted AMIs. This value can be any of the following:

    • KMS key ID
    • KMS key alias
    • ARN referring to the KMS key ID
    • ARN referring to the KMS key alias

    If encrypted is enabled but a KMS key ID is not specified, the customer's default KMS key for Amazon EBS is used.

  • frequency :: Maybe Int

    The frequency of creating replication jobs for the server.

  • runOnce :: Maybe Bool

    Indicates whether to run the replication job one time.

  • licenseType :: Maybe LicenseType

    The license type for creating a replication job for the server.
